<br />
seriously..<br />
<br />
VI released a "Game", which you pay for them to support (I know, please don't laugh).<br />
A "Game" designed for enjoyment and not as a profession.  <br />
<br />
To put an example of this in another case, you can rent an apartment and it may have a clause that prohibits any business from being run from it you can not even "charge for your time" <br />
<br />
In this case, you are renting online time in an online world, and there is a clause about making money from it.<br />
<br />
seems simple to me: their game, their world , their rules.... If you don't like the noise, leave the party, others here are having fun.</font></p>
             
