             </font> 
            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">Selling anything that is virtual is always in a grey area... you can argue both ways, because value is hard to see.<br />
<br />
The key is defining value (based on what I hear from people and personal experience)<br />
<br />
1) Value in eq would be the charactor's level, gear, and pp.  <br />
2) Value is reputation, friends, guild relations are more valuable to them.  <br />
3) Fun is the value gain from playing eq.  <br />
<br />
You can have combination of 2 or 3 of these value ideas.  The time and the effort (of leveling, camping for loot, interaction with people, building an reputation, etc) invested into eq create these values.<br />
<br />
To support for one who agree with selling the account... <br />
<br />
You are purchasing an account... aren't you in fact also purchasing their reputation, friends, guild relations... as well as the known charactor's levels, skills, gears, and pp.... plus now you can have fun too.  <br />
<br />
(This is based on if the person that sold the charactor did not tell their guild, friends, etc that they are leaving and selling the account.)<br />
<br />
To support for one who disagree with selling the account...<br />
<br />
There is no value to be gain from purchasing the virtual items...  the real value is gain from experiencing the game like the leveling the charactor from 1 to 65 and collecting gears, exploring new zones, meeting new people and chatting with friends.  These are the things that makes the game fun: the value of the game.<br />
<br />
(This is based on if the person that bought the charactor never play eq before)<br />
<br />
To me, I think the key to value is fun... if person aren't having fun, why would people quit the game and sell the account... as well why would people buy the account and keep on playing if they don't think it is fun.<br />
<br />
The rules listed by Verant/Sony about selling account is a way for them to sell more package games and open more account... maybe for marketing purpose (like look we sold 1,000,000 acounts instead of selling about half of it while those that quit just sell the account to another person).  It is also a control for them if account is hacked, they can trace who the original owner is.  <br />
<br />
For the selling of virtual items, it is just a mess to deal with.  For those who traded goods in the old bazaar in EC would know (price haggling, giving a person pp for an item but got something else in return, etc  imagine all that in real life exchanging the pp with real money and buying items that depriecate faster then Canadian doller <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""> ).  The staff at Verant/Sony already have problem keeping up with customer support they don't want to add more problems.</font></p>
             
            <p></p>
