            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">VI had an easy time going after sights such as Ebay, all they needed to do was have their lawyers contact Ebays and the problem is easily fixed.  The reasoning behind why they havent just shut this guy down with a couple of lawsuits is 1) they may not be sure they can win as internet law is up in the air currently and 2) while you probably could get a cease and desist in the US, whats to stop him from taking his service overseas to one of the data havens, thus making it even harder for them to track.  The other major issue that could arise is the Microsoft effect--you get too big all your competitors come out of the woodwork to go against you--and with Sony having the biggest share of the pie and with the mechanics of their world being what they are the most to lose.  Or it could just come down to the fact that they have a timeline in place, with a New Game in the works where this kind of thing would be very difficult to duplicate. Take your pick.</font></p>
             
