            <p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="1">Personally I could not give a trolls arse if someone sells their character...what pisses me off is when someone buys a character. Sounds dumb I know...but the pissed off part comes in when the buyer A) F's up BIG time cause they are a clueless moron when it comes to strategies and capabilities of this new character of theirs, and...B) when they start strutting and acting tough (cause of their level and equipment) when THEY did not earn or deserve squat.<br />
<br />
SOE and VI should ALLOW character sales. They could act as an escrow officer. Both parties agree and cash or plat is traded, both petition a GM and the character (s) are transferred to the new account, it's on the record, neither knows the others passwords...and SOE/VI collects a fee.<br />
<br />
I'd also like to see a program where you could trade in characters to SOE/VI, such as I have a 50 paladin and I think I'd rather have an SK...and SOE/VI gives you a 25 SK with maxed skills for the 25th level...you keep plat and equipment from pally (since YOU earned it). <br />
<br />
I think you call that an "idea"...Damn, my head hurts now!<img src="images/smilies/biggrin.gif" border="0" alt=""></font></p>
             
